    <RimTalk.Settings.TTS.RuleEditor.Help>How to Use:

1. Adding Requirements:
   - Click buttons in the lower-left panel to add requirements
   - Upper-left panel shows selected requirements
   - Click × to remove requirements

2. Adding Voice Models:
   - Click voice models in the lower-right panel to add them
   - Upper-right panel shows selected voice models
   - Click × to remove voice models
   - One voice will be randomly selected from the selected voices when matched

3. Matching Logic:
   - Same type requirements automatically use "OR" logic
     Example: Selecting both "Male" and "Female" will match all male or female characters
   - Different type results use "AND" logic
     Example: Selecting "Male", "Baseliner", "Hussars", and "Age 20-30" will match male characters aged 20-30 who are either Baseliner or Hussars
   - Empty type = always matches

4. Overall Rule Priority (unrelated to this window, refers to the main settings rule logic):
   - Evaluates characters from top to bottom
   - Randomly selects one voice from the first matched rule
   - Use ↑↓ buttons to adjust priority</RimTalk.Settings.TTS.RuleEditor.Help>

